# PROJECT: slint-gui-mcp

## Goal
A Windows-only MCP server written in Rust that gives AI assistants (e.g. Claude Code) vision
and control of a running GUI window. Solves the problem of AIs guessing UI positions by
providing direct visual feedback and image-based interaction via template matching —
no coordinates needed, AI sends a crop of the UI element and the server finds and clicks it.

## Stack
- Language: Rust (stable, edition 2021)
- MCP protocol: rmcp 0.1 (community crate, server + transport-io features)
- Window capture: windows crate 0.58 (Win32 HWND-based)
- Image processing: image 0.25, imageproc 0.25 (template matching via NCC)
- Input: enigo 0.2 (mouse + keyboard, cross-platform)
- Serialisation: serde 1, serde_json 1, base64 0.22
- Async runtime: tokio 1 (full features — required by rmcp)
- Build scanners: rustdocumenter, rustscanners (git deps)

## Structure
- src:    src/
- state:  src/state/
- proj:   proj/
- docs:   doc/

## Method
- Workflow: PROJECT → FIXES → TODO → code → cargo build → test → DONE
- Branching: feature branches, never commit to main
- Testing: cargo test
- Deploy: single binary, no runtime dependencies

## Patterns
- window-find: EnumWindows with partial case-insensitive title match → HWND
- image-capture: GetWindowDC + CreateCompatibleBitmap + BitBlt → BGRA → RgbImage
- template-match: Normalized cross-correlation (NCC) over RgbImage pairs
- mcp-tool: #[tool(tool_box)] impl on server struct, one async fn per MCP tool
- constants: All literal values (thresholds, timeouts) in src/state/ — never inline

